        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/df705f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-12-03T23:44:50.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Good fill into base neck.</p>\n<p>Quite a bit of color variation, from watery rim to orange to garnet to medium red.</p>\n<p>A nicely aromatic nose of cigar ash, cocoa, smoke, nuts, wet forest floor, and faint amounts of blood orange and red currants. Also a slight metallic note.</p>\n<p>One of the first impressions on the palate is a nice honeyed sweetness, with further impressions of a silky palate - nicely resolved tannins - a red earth quality and mild flavors of red fruits: currants again and cherry and strawberry.</p>\n<p>Quite fine. (Doggone good.)</p>\n<p>Anyone know why the metallic aroma would be there? I have noticed it before in other older Bordeauxes.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T20:35:17.677Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
