      {
        "id": 2070460,
        "name": "Karl K@zaks",
        "username": "Karl_K",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/df705f/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-12-04T05:31:52.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Arv R\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Arv R:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I had some strong metallic notes on some 1970 Magdelaine\u2019s.  Others who were familiar with the estate didn\u2019t pick them up, or it didn\u2019t bother them as we drank, but it was always weird to me.  I thought there was a flaw, or damage.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I have had that wine, found it very nice, and may have noted metallic there. But I do know I did not expose it to air long (not because I didn\u2019t want to, but because of circumstances) which could point to reduction.</p>",
